==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[propwash]] [[deflection]] [[unit]]}}

# A Propwash Deflection Unit, also known as a ''PDU'' or ''deflector'' is a device that is placed over or behind the propeller of a boat to deflect the vessel's propwash downward.  The result is a very effective form of agitation dredging.  PDUs are primarily used by salvors to remove mud or sand from shallow water shipwrecks.

